This paper is about training convolutional neural networks with low-bit quantization, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories of computer science. The most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as these are the areas where neural network training and optimization are typically studied. The sub-categories cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) are also possible, as they are relevant to the computational aspects of training neural networks.
